cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computer and Society (cs.CY) as it deals with privacy and user data. It could also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the accuracy of Google's demographic inferences. Additionally, it could be classified under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with user behavior and usage characteristics. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses how Google infers user data. Finally, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with user privacy and how users interact with Google's Ad Settings.
